    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>The google collections framework offers quote a good transform method,so you can transform your Objects into Strings. The only downside is that it has to be from Iterable to Iterable but this is the way I would do it:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Iterable&lt;Object&gt; objects = ....... //Your chosen iterable here\nIterable&lt;String&gt; strings = com.google.common.collect.Iterables.transform(objects, new Function&lt;Object, String&gt;(){\n        String apply(Object from){\n             return from.toString();\n        }\n });\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This take you away from using arrays,but I think this would be my prefered way. </p>\n"
  }, {
